\left(x + y\right)^n = \sum_{\epsilon_1, \ldots, \epsilon_n \in \{0,1\}} x \left(x + \sum_{j=1}^n \epsilon_j z_j\right)^{\left(\sum_{j=1}^n \epsilon_j\right) - 1} \left(y - \sum_{j=1}^n \epsilon_j z_j\right)^{n - \left(\sum_{j=1}^n \epsilon_j\right)}
